Description: Limestone canopic jar; human-headed lid affixed to the body; four columns of incised Hieroglyphic text within a panel.
Curator's comments: The jar formed part of a set with EA 36534, EA 36537 and EA 36539. The source of the group, 'Sm', is noted only on the Birch slip for EA 36539 [E.S. 639], but all four jars are inscribed with the same name and they are listed as a set in the 3 volume MS catalogue of the Sams Collection (AES archive).
